commentTextItems.html: there it is! Dhoni dances down the track and swings across, gets it on the middle and the ball sails over the midwicket fence, that's his 10th six of the innings and India have won in grand style

commentPostTextItems.html: What an innings!  this now is the highest score by a wicket-keeper in ODIs beating Gilchrist's 172!
298 looked a massive total when the chase started but thanks to some scintillating stroke play from Dhoni India have reached the target in just 46.1 overs.
Dravid took a gamble by sending in Dhoni and he hit the jackpot.
For the latest bulletin on today's play, features and other stories please visit www.cricinfo.com
Do write in with any feedback at http://www.cricinfo.com/commentary.html
Dhoni started off in smashing fashion and there was no looking back, each and every bowler went for runs - a total of 11 sixes and 24 boundaries were hit during the course of this amazing run chase.
India now lead the series 3-0 with four more games left in the series.

Marvan Atapattu - 'we had a good chance - these wickets are pretty much flat but when somebody plays an innings like that it's out of control - It's didn't matter whether we took the power play or not - he is that kind of a player
we haven't won a single game but we hope that we will come back as soon as we can.
Dravid - 'Unbelievable stuff' - 'All of us here were privileged to watch such an innings, fantastic knock - We went into the dressing room and we believed we could get it
- 'Sangakkara and Jayawardene batted well for them and Sangakkara in particular did well but he was outdone by the other wicket keeper.
'after my 148 this was expected of me, I am happy with the number three position, but i am happy to play where ever the team management decides'
Hope you have enjoyed the coverage - until next time this is Sajan Nair signing off - Cheers!

Dhoni gets the Man of the match for his brilliant innings of 183*-  'Actually when the first ball was bowled i read the wicket - as the game progressed it became flat - It was a long innings for me - i kept for 50 overs and batted for a time so it was tough for me

commentTextItems.html: another good length delivery outside the off stump, no shot offered

commentPostTextItems.html: India require another 2 runs with 6 wickets and 24 balls remaining

commentTextItems.html: make that 9 ! this one is lofted over the long-off fence
inside out shot and the ball balloons up towards deep extra cover

tossed up outside the off stump, Dhoni steps forward and lofts it away handsomely over the extra cover fence for his 8th six - this now is the record for the highest number of sixes by an Indian in ODIs
tossed up and drifting down the leg side, Dhoni gets forward and turns it away fine to the fine leg region - cheeky shot as they call it
good length delivery outside the off stump, stopped a bit and Rao is beaten outside the off stump

milestones.description: MS Dhoni has broken the record for most sixes in an innings (10) in ODIs for IND, going past Tendulkar's 7
MS Dhoni has broken the record for most runs in boundaries (120) in an innings in ODIs for IND, going past Ganguly's 110

stories.title: Dhoni: Basic instinct
stories.subTitle: India v Sri Lanka, 3rd ODI, Jaipur
stories.summary: If anyone had doubts about Dhoni's ability with the bat - not merely as a mighty biffer of the ball but as a batsman fully worthy of a top-order slot - then they have been erased

stories.title: The wheel turns, and how
stories.subTitle: India v Sri Lanka, 3rd ODI, Jaipur
stories.summary: What Mahendra Singh Dhoni did to Sri Lanka was similar to what Sri Lanka, under Arjuna Ranatunga, did to most, and some controlled methods amid electrifying mayhem put everything else in the shade
